
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `driverless-fax` baraye ersal va daryaft fax az tarigh terminal, bedoon niaz be nasb driver-haye khas estefade mishavad. In dastoor az protocol-haye standard interneti mesle IPP (Internet Printing Protocol) baraye ertebat ba device fax estefade mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `driverless-fax send --recipient <shomare-fax> <file>` --> 📤 Ersal yek file be yek shomare fax moshakhas.
    🔹 `driverless-fax receive` --> 📥 Daryaft fax-haye vared shode (agar device fax ghabeliat daryaft ro dashte bashe).
    🔹 `driverless-fax list-devices` --> 🔎 List kardan device haye fax-e dastras dar shabake.
    🔹 `driverless-fax --help` --> ❓ Namayesh rahnamaye dastoor va gozine-haye digar.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ driverless-fax send --recipient 123456789 mydocument.pdf

    🔹 Ersal file `mydocument.pdf` be shomare fax `123456789`.

    $ driverless-fax receive

    🔹 Daryaft fax-haye vared shode va zakhire anha.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ driverless-fax list-devices

    🔹  Liste device haye fax-e dastras dar shabake ra namayesh midahad. Shoma mitoonid az in list baraye moshakhas kardan device mored nazar dar zaman ersal ya daryaft estefade konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `driverless-fax` command is used to send and receive faxes from the terminal without needing specific drivers. It uses standard internet protocols like IPP (Internet Printing Protocol) to communicate with fax devices.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `driverless-fax send --recipient <fax-number> <file>` --> 📤 Send a file to a specific fax number.
    🔹 `driverless-fax receive` --> 📥 Receive incoming faxes (if the fax device supports receiving).
    🔹 `driverless-fax list-devices` --> 🔎 List available fax devices on the network.
    🔹 `driverless-fax --help` --> ❓ Display command help and other options.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ driverless-fax send --recipient 123456789 mydocument.pdf

    🔹 Sends the file `mydocument.pdf` to the fax number `123456789`.

    $ driverless-fax receive

    🔹 Receives incoming faxes and saves them.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ driverless-fax list-devices

    🔹 Displays a list of available fax devices on the network. You can use this list to specify the desired device when sending or receiving faxes.
